<H1 ALIGN=JUSTIFY><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif">Converter</FONT></H1>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif"><B>Converter</B>
makes possible to run several utilities able to convert some <B>Term
Suite</B> processing results in XMI format into human readable file
formats. It provides 4 converters for the following 2 kinds of
conversion:</FONT></P>
<UL>
	<LI><P ALIGN=JUSTIFY><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif"><B>XMI
	</B>→<B>TSV</B> that converts files in XMI format into TSV  format
	i.e. in “tabulated-separated value” format, 1 line per word and
	3 rows per line respectively for the word, its grammatical category
	and its lemma.</FONT></P>
	<LI><P ALIGN=JUSTIFY><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif"><B>TSV
	</B>→<B>XMI</B> that processes backwards a monolingual corpora
	provided by a third-part tool in the “tabulated-separated value”
	file format and provides XMI files with the corresponding word
	annotations with category and lemma features.</FONT></P>
	<LI><P ALIGN=JUSTIFY><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif"><B>XMI
	</B>→<B>TBX</B> <SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal">that converts a
	XMI terminology into a TermBase eXchange one. </SPAN></FONT>
	</P>
	<LI><P ALIGN=JUSTIFY><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><B>TBX
	</B></SPAN><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal">→</SPAN></SPAN><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><B>XMI</B></SPAN><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal"><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: normal">
	that converts backwards a TermBase eXchange terminology into a XMI
	one.</SPAN></SPAN></FONT></P>
</UL>
<H2 CLASS="western"><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif"><I>XMI
→TSV</I></FONT></H2>
<H3 CLASS="western" STYLE="font-style: normal"><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif"><FONT SIZE=3>Settings</FONT></FONT></H3>
<P STYLE="font-style: normal"><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif">This
converter requires the following 2 parameters to be set:</FONT></P>
<UL>
	<LI><P><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif"><I>Input Directory</I></FONT><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal">:
	the directory of the XMI files;</SPAN></FONT></P>
	<LI><P><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif"><I>Output Directory</I></FONT><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal">:
	the directory of the TSV files. </SPAN></FONT>
	</P>
</UL>
